<p>GDP growth: 5.3% GDP: $584bn (PPP: $726bn) Inflation: 4.3% Population: 28.9m GDP per head: $20,220 (PPP: $25,130)</p>

<p>Arab-spring tides have barely washed Saudi shores; old age and poor health will continue to be the drivers of change. The king is pushing 90, and potential successors are elderly and no less conservative. The economy will benefit from the decision to pump extra oil in 2011. Capital investments and social spending  will keep growth strong.</p>

